The Ground-Based Air Defense Directed Energy On-the-Move program, known as GBAD, is being designed for use on light tactical vehicles such as the Humvee and Joint Light Tactical Vehicle .
The system will be able to spot and track drones, then shoot them out of the sky using a 30kw laser as a stepping stone to firing .
Some of the systems already have been used in tests to detect and track UAVs of all sizes .